{"type":"message","id":"62b3a0ab","parentId":"13bc7cb0","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:22:49.774Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_sttiv6r9zpwu_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5507\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=4057\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 032214 - The TIC Experiment requires implementing a classifier on pulse logs. I need to first understand the structure of existing pulse logs to design the classifier properly.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"keen-falcon","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5507\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=4057\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 032214 - The TIC Experiment requires implementing a classifier on pulse logs. I need to first understand the structure of existing pulse logs to design the classifier properly.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774336969772}}
{"type":"message","id":"2880a092","parentId":"62b3a0ab","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:22:49.777Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_sttiv6r9zpwu_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 032015\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best action.\r\n\r\nThe current situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 (architecture analysis) are complete\r\n- Key insight: Compression and Causal Discovery are the same problem\r\n- Next action identified: TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment\r\n- Need to implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nThe pending TIC Experiment requires:\r\n1. Implementing TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n2. Measuring invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n3. Predicting next pulse content from invariants\r\n4. Validating against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe immediate next action should be to start implementing the TIC experiment. The most concrete first step would be to:\r\n1. Read the existing pulse logs to understand their structure\r\n2. Create the TIC implementation\r\n\r\nLooking at the notes, the last pulse was `pulse_2026-03-24 031816.md`. Let me check what files exist and implement the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action I can take now is to:\r\n1. Check the logs directory structure\r\n2. Create a TIC classifier script that can analyze the pulse logs\r\n\r\nLet me start by examining the logs and creating the TIC implementation.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next priority, requiring analysis of existing pulse logs to test the compression-causal duality hypothesis. I need to first examine the pulse log structure and then implement the classifier.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier implementation to analyze pulse logs for invariant/variant classification. This implements the core Phase 1 advancement hypothesis that causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n# Tests Hypothesis: Causal structure = Invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Tuple\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nclass TICClassifier:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Temporal Invariance Compression Classifier.\r\n    \r\n    Hypothesis: The compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n    Session gaps = decay mechanism = compression.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    \r\n    def __init__(self, logs_dir: str = \"logs\"):\r\n        self.logs_dir = Path(logs_dir)\r\n        self.λ = 0.7  # Decay/gap sensitivity parameter (from goals)\r\n        \r\n    def load_pulses(self) -> List[Dict]:\r\n        \"\"\"Load all pulse log files.\"\"\"\r\n        pulses = []\r\n        for f in sorted(self.logs_dir.glob(\"pulse_*.md\")):\r\n            content = f.read_text()\r\n            pulses.append({\r\n                'file': f.name,\r\n                'content': content,\r\n                'timestamp': self._extract_timestamp(f.name)\r\n            })\r\n        return pulses\r\n    \r\n    def _extract_timestamp(self, filename: str) -> str:\r\n        \"\"\"Extract timestamp from pulse filename.\"\"\"\r\n        match = re.search(r'pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}_\\d{6})\\.md', filename)\r\n        return match.group(1) if match else \"\"\r\n    \r\n    def _tokenize(self, text: str) -> List[str]:\r\n        \"\"\"Simple tokenization for comparison.\"\"\"\r\n        return re.findall(r'\\b\\w+\\b', text.lower())\r\n    \r\n    def compute_invariants(self, pulses: List[Dict]) -> Dict[str, float]:\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        Find invariant structures across pulse sequence.\r\n        Returns: {token: invariance_score}\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        if len(pulses) < 2:\r\n            return {}\r\n        \r\n        # Count token frequencies across all pulses\r\n        token_counts = Counter()\r\n        pulse_tokens = []\r\n        \r\n        for p in pulses:\r\n            tokens = self._tokenize(p['content'])\r\n            pulse_tokens.append(set(tokens))\r\n            for t in tokens:\r\n                token_counts[t] += 1\r\n        \r\n        # Invariance score = appears in % of pulses\r\n        n_pulses = len(pulses)\r\n        invariants = {}\r\n        \r\n        for token, count in token_counts.items():\r\n            invariance = count / n_pulses\r\n            if invariance >= self.λ:\r\n                invariants[token] = invariance\r\n        \r\n        return invariants\r\n    \r\n    def classify_pulse(self, pulse: Dict, invariants: Dict[str, float]) -> Dict:\r\n        \"\"\"Classify pulse content as invariant or variant.\"\"\"\r\n        tokens = self._tokenize(pulse['content'])\r\n        \r\n        invariant_tokens = [t for t in tokens if t in invariants]\r\n        variant_tokens = [t for t in tokens if t not in invariants]\r\n        \r\n        total = len(tokens) or 1\r\n        inv_ratio = len(invariant_tokens) / total\r\n        \r\n        return {\r\n            'invariant_ratio': inv_ratio,\r\n            'variant_ratio': 1 - inv_ratio,\r\n            'classified_as': 'invariant' if inv_ratio >= 0.5 else 'variant'\r\n        }\r\n    \r\n    def predict_next(self, current: Dict, invariants: Dict) -> str:\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        Predict characteristics of next pulse based on invariants.\r\n        Returns: prediction string\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        if not invariants:\r\n            return \"No invariants established - prediction unreliable\"\r\n        \r\n        top_invariants = sorted(invariants.items(), key=lambda x: -x[1])[:10]\r\n        inv_list = ', '.join([f\"{t}({s:.0%})\" for t, s in top_invariants])\r\n        \r\n        return f\"Next pulse should maintain: {inv_list}\"\r\n    \r\n    def run_experiment(self) -> Dict:\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        Run full TIC experiment on pulse logs.\r\n        Returns: results dict with classification accuracy and predictions\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        pulses = self.load_pulses()\r\n        \r\n        if len(pulses) < 3:\r\n            return {'\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 03:20:53\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774336969774}}
