{"type":"message","id":"ecbd0d12","parentId":"fd4f9303","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:23:13.579Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The newest file is `pulse_2026-03-24 032214.md`, but this is just the one being processed. The one I read earlier was `pulse_2026-03-24 032015.md`. Let me read the newest one to see the full results of this pulse.","thinkingSignature":"454f24370fd84450addd993ef2b6f2bf9f6056e4c12360251b57cbef752a1a2f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3awft3ltu2bm_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 032214.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2349,"output":118,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14421,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774336988646}}
{"type":"message","id":"03bcd1d0","parentId":"ecbd0d12","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:23:13.585Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_3awft3ltu2bm_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 032214\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what single concrete action I should take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked complete\r\n2. The big pending action is the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment\r\n3. The next action requires:\r\n   - Implementing TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n   - Measuring invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n   - Predicting next pulse content from invariants\r\n   - Validating against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThis is a substantial experiment. Let me think about what concrete action I can take:\r\n\r\n1. I need to examine the existing pulse logs to understand the format\r\n2. I need to implement the TIC classifier\r\n3. I need to run experiments\r\n\r\nLet me start by looking at the pulse logs to understand their structure, then implement a basic TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nFirst, let me check what pulse logs exist and their format.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC Experiment requires implementing a classifier on pulse logs. I need to first understand the structure of existing pulse logs to design the classifier properly.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier implementation by first examining existing pulse logs for structure, then implementing the invariant/variant classification logic.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\n# Hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nimport hashlib\r\nfrom datetime import datetime\r\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Tuple, Set\r\n\r\nclass PulseLog:\r\n    \"\"\"Represents a single pulse log entry\"\"\"\r\n    def __init__(self, filepath: str):\r\n        self.path = filepath\r\n        self.name = os.path.basename(filepath)\r\n        # Extract timestamp from filename: pulse_2026-03-24 032015.md\r\n        match = re.search(r'pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2})_(\\d{6})', self.name)\r\n        if match:\r\n            self.date = match.group(1)\r\n            self.time = match.group(2)\r\n            self.timestamp = f\"{self.date} {self.time[:2]}:{self.time[2:4]}:{self.time[4:6]}\"\r\n        \r\n        with open(filepath, 'r') as f:\r\n            self.content = f.read()\r\n        \r\n        # Extract sections\r\n        self.sections = self._parse_sections()\r\n        \r\n    def _parse_sections(self) -> Dict[str, str]:\r\n        \"\"\"Parse markdown sections\"\"\"\r\n        sections = {}\r\n        current_header = \"header\"\r\n        current_content = []\r\n        \r\n        for line in self.content.split('\\n'):\r\n            if line.startswith('### '):\r\n                if current_header:\r\n                    sections[current_header] = '\\n'.join(current_content)\r\n                current_header = line[4:].strip()\r\n                current_content = []\r\n            else:\r\n                current_content.append(line)\r\n        \r\n        if current_header:\r\n            sections[current_header] = '\\n'.join(current_content)\r\n        \r\n        return sections\r\n    \r\n    def get_tokens(self) -> Set[str]:\r\n        \"\"\"Extract meaningful tokens from pulse\"\"\"\r\n        # Simple token extraction - words with length > 3\r\n        text = self.content.lower()\r\n        tokens = set(re.findall(r'\\b[a-z]{4,}\\b', text))\r\n        return tokens\r\n\r\n\r\nclass TICClassifier:\r\n    \"\"\"Temporal Invariance Compression Classifier\"\"\"\r\n    \r\n    def __init__(self, log_dir: str = \"logs\"):\r\n        self.log_dir = log_dir\r\n        self.pulses: List[PulseLog] = []\r\n        self.invariant_tokens: Set[str] = set()  # Persistent across pulses\r\n        self.variant_tokens: Set[str] = set()     # Session-specific\r\n        self.λ = 0.7  # Decay/gap sensitivity parameter\r\n        \r\n    def load_pulses(self, limit: int = 20) -> None:\r\n        \"\"\"Load pulse logs, most recent first\"\"\"\r\n        log_files = sorted([f for f in os.listdir(self.log_dir) if f.startswith('pulse_') and f.endswith('.md')])\r\n        log_files = log_files[-limit:]  # Last N pulses\r\n        \r\n        for f in log_files:\r\n            self.pulses.append(PulseLog(os.path.join(self.log_dir, f)))\r\n        \r\n        print(f\"Loaded {len(self.pulses)} pulses\")\r\n        \r\n    def compute_invariants(self) -> Dict[str, float]:\r\n        \"\"\"Identify tokens that persist across sessions (invariants)\"\"\"\r\n        if len(self.pulses) < 2:\r\n            return {}\r\n        \r\n        token_presence = {}  # token -> list of pulse indices where it appears\r\n        \r\n        for i, pulse in enumerate(self.pulses):\r\n            tokens = pulse.get_tokens()\r\n            for token in tokens:\r\n                if token not in token_presence:\r\n                    token_presence[token] = []\r\n                token_presence[token].append(i)\r\n        \r\n        # Invariant = appears in >70% of pulses OR consistently across gap\r\n        invariant_scores = {}\r\n        n = len(self.pulses)\r\n        \r\n        for token, appearances in token_presence.items():\r\n            # Calculate persistence ratio\r\n            persistence = len(appearances) / n\r\n            \r\n            # Calculate gap behavior - prefer tokens that survive session boundaries\r\n            gaps_survived = 0\r\n            for i in range(len(appearances) - 1):\r\n                if appearances[i+1] - appearances[i] <= 3:  # Within 3 pulses\r\n                    gaps_survived += 1\r\n            \r\n            gap_survival_rate = gaps_survived / max(len(appearances) - 1, 1)\r\n            \r\n            # Combined score: persistence +\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 03:22:49\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774336993583}}
